      • createWithoutPaymentMethod

        @JvmStatic
 @JvmOverloads
 @NotNull
public static ConfirmSetupIntentParams createWithoutPaymentMethod(@NotNull
                                                                                                      java.lang.String clientSecret,
                                                                                                      @Nullable
                                                                                                      java.lang.String returnUrl)

        Create the parameters necessary for confirming a SetupIntent, without specifying a payment method to attach to the SetupIntent. Only use this if a payment method has already been attached to the SetupIntent.

        Parameters:
        clientSecret - The client secret of this SetupIntent. Used for client-side retrieval using a publishable key.
        returnUrl - The URL to redirect your customer back to after they authenticate on the payment method’s app or site.If you’d prefer to redirect to a mobile application, you can alternatively supply an application URI scheme.This parameter is only used for cards and other redirect-based payment methods.
        Returns:
        params that can be use to confirm a SetupIntent

      • create

        @JvmStatic
 @JvmOverloads
 @NotNull
public static ConfirmSetupIntentParams create(@NotNull
                                                                                  java.lang.String paymentMethodId,
                                                                                  @NotNull
                                                                                  java.lang.String clientSecret,
                                                                                  @Nullable
                                                                                  java.lang.String returnUrl,
                                                                                  @Nullable
                                                                                  java.lang.String mandateId,
                                                                                  @Nullable
                                                                                  MandateDataParams mandateData)

        Create the parameters necessary for confirming a SetupIntent while attaching a PaymentMethod that already exits.

        Parameters:
        paymentMethodId - ID of the payment method (a PaymentMethod, Card, BankAccount, orsaved Source object) to attach to this SetupIntent.
        clientSecret - The client secret of this SetupIntent. Used for client-side retrieval using a publishable key.
        returnUrl - The URL to redirect your customer back to after they authenticate on the payment method’s app or site.If you’d prefer to redirect to a mobile application, you can alternatively supply an application URI scheme.This parameter is only used for cards and other redirect-based payment methods.
        mandateId - optional ID of the Mandate to be used for this payment.
        mandateData - optional details about the Mandate to create.
        Returns:
        params that can be use to confirm a SetupIntent
